Package: picam-frontend
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Multi-Pi WebRTC web viewer for picam-orchestrator backends
 Single web UI that can view and switch between multiple picam-orchestrator
 backends (one per Pi) from a single page. Live video is WebRTC (VP8);
 since that's peer-to-peer by nature, this process is a small SFU-lite
 relay for the media path (terminates WebRTC with both the browser and
 each picam-orchestrator, forwarding raw RTP packets between them — no
 decode/re-encode) rather than a byte proxy. Status JSON is still a plain
 proxy. Browsers never connect directly to any Pi, only to this frontend.
 .
 Configure the list of Pis in /etc/picam-frontend/config.ini under
 the [pis] section. Each Pi just needs picam-orchestrator installed and
 reachable on the network; no other configuration is required on
 the Pi side.
 .
 Open http://<this-host> in a browser to view.
 .
 Config: /etc/picam-frontend/config.ini
